member.name: M:MUnique.OpenMU.Persistence.Json.ReferenceResolvingConverter`1.ResolveObjectReference(System.Text.Json.JsonSerializerOptions,System.String)
member.summary: Resolves the object reference by the reference handler of the serializer.
member.returns: The resolved object.
member.remarks: The idea here is, to handle $ref and $id the same; If it's a $ref, there are two cases: - the object was read before: it's all logical, we use the previously read object. - the object wasn't read before (e.g. circular reference): We already create the object as a placeholder, so that when $id comes along, it can be filled. If it's an $id, there are also two cases: - the object was created before by a $ref: all fine, we take and fill it - the object wasn't created before: we create a new one. This implies, that any object should have $id as first property.
